commit.message:
docs: fix simple typo, underneat -> underneath

There is a small typo in pyvim/layout.py.

Should read `underneath` rather than `underneat`.

Fix the F9 key binding in the example pyvimrc

This fixes the "editor_buffer.filename is None" issue as well as
an issue with running the command in a subprocess.
Loosen grammar to allow for missing parentheses
Set cursor position after replacement to last selected range
Add test for range specification's boundary condition
Fix exception on repeat substitution without substitution
Add test for repeating substitution pattern from substitute history
Add test for :s's 'g' flag and fix empty flags case
Fix cursor position after :substitute with line number
Fix for directory listing on Python 2. Pygments expects a string.

Fix ResourceWarning: unclosed file in setup.py

Signed-off-by: Mickal Schoentgen <contact@tiger-222.fr>
Fixed width of welcome message (prompt_toolkit version was partly invisible).
Implement '-' key binding in file explorer mode.
